    "li": [
      "PHP",
      "Log in to the application. Open the application and authenticate. Navigate to pages that use sessions to make sure that a session is created.",
      "Verify that session cookies have the \"secure\" flag set. Use the web browser to view stored cookies. Make sure that the application session ID cookie has the \"secure\" flag set.",
      "Check the php.ini file. If testing with a browser is not appropriate, check the php.ini file to make sure the \"session.cookie_secure\" directive is set to \"On\".",
      "Verify that SSL is available. The \"secure\" flag forces cookies to be sent over SSL. SSL has to be available for this to work.",
      "Configure PHP to set the \"secure\" flag on session cookies. Edit the php.ini file and configure the \"session.cookie_secure\" setting, like this:\r\n        session.cookie_secure = On",
      "For more information about the session_set_cookie_params function, please see http://php.net/manual/en/function.session-set-cookie-params.php",
